wikipedia_page.main: Joseph Rank (28 March 1854 – 13 November 1943) was the founder of Joseph Rank Limited, once  one of Britain's largest Flour milling and bakery companies. He built his company into a leader in all aspects of  the industry including the operation of Flour Mills, Bakeries and Retail outlets. After Rank's death in 1943 the company continued to grow under his son's stewardship before merging with Hovis MacDougall in the 1960s to form Rank Hovis McDougall (RHM).
